  <!-- Standing keyframe (round 7).

       Round 6 fixed CAD-export noise + the model's intrinsic mass
       asymmetry (waist body inertial pos = -0.00188 m in x → CoM 6 mm
       ahead of mid-feet) by tilting the pelvis -0.020 rad and using a
       symmetric joint pose with knees ≈ 0.023 rad.  That settled at
       ~0.0001 m/s drift but used a near-straight-legs pose that did
       NOT match the walking q_ref[0] (bent knees ≈ 0.49 rad).  The
       resulting standing-to-walking ramp then had to drop the body
       ~10 mm and bend knees ~0.46 rad in 1 s — which itself
       generated transients the C2 harness had to fight.

       Round 7 takes a different approach: bake the walking pose
       (q_ref[0] of the multi-cycle plan) directly into the home key,
       with the pelvis settled to its physics equilibrium under
       ctrl=qpos.  After this, the standing-to-walking ramp is a
       no-op (max Δ ≈ 0).  The body starts at the prior's t=0 state
       and the 50-step ramp simply stabilizes the walking pose.

       Verified: 1000 physics steps with ctrl=qpos → pelvis drift
       ~0.0004 m, |vx| ≤ 0.0002 m/s, z stable at 0.4575 m.

       Geometry note: this keyframe is paired with the round-7
       refitted IK (upper_leg=0.193, lower_leg=0.180,
